Jakarta share index hits record 700 . 89 pts . The Jakarta composite share index hit a record 700 . 89 points in late afternoon trading on Wednesday on blue chip buying , brokers said . Further fresh overseas buying of blue - chip stocks after the afternoon session opened helped push the index up , brokers said . They said Bank Negara Indonesia and cigarette makers Sampoerna and Gudang Garam were the main buying targets . Brokers said the Jakarta bourse might also benefit from a spill - over effect after they said an American securities house in the region revised its buying programme . - - Jakarta newsroom + 6221 384 - 6364 
